cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR 

This paper presents a Bayesian framework for learning probabilistic specifications from code corpora and using it to detect anomalous program behavior. The paper focuses on software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) by proposing a method to statically detect program errors. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as topic modeling and neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the problem of computing a distance between distributions, which is relevant to cryptography (cs.CR).
